tafsir[13]{c,v,t}:
  69,36,"Neither will he have any food to eat except the fluid flowing from the bodies of the people of the hellfire."
  69,37,"Only the sinners will eat from that food."
  69,38,"Allah takes an oath on whatever you see."
  69,39,"And He also takes an oath on whatever you cannot see."
  69,41,"It is not the speech of a poet because it is not on the pattern of a poem; little do you believe!"
  69,42,"Neither is it the speech of a fortune teller because the speech of fortune tellers is different to that of this Qur’ān; little do you take heed!"
  69,45,"I would definitely take forceful and due retribution from him."
  69,46,"Then I would cut the vein connected to his heart."
  69,49,"And I know that there are definitely people among you who reject this Qur’ān."
  70,2,"It will fall upon the disbelievers in Allah. There will be no one to avert this punishment."
  70,4,"The angels and Gabriel will ascend in them ranks on the Day of Judgement: it is a day of which the duration is fifty thousand years."
  70,5,"O Messenger! So be patient; a patience free of worry and complaint."
  70,7,"But I see it as being near and inevitably occurring."